<BaseLayout title="About — Yahor Bezzubau" description="Yahor Bezzubau — Staff Engineer at JetBrains, writing about AI agents, TypeScript, and platform engineering.">
  <article class="about">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>
      I'm <strong>Yahor Bezzubau</strong> — a Staff Engineer at <a href="https://www.jetbrains.com" target="_blank">JetBrains</a>,
      working on <strong>Kineto</strong>. Based in the Netherlands.
    </p>

    <p>
      I've spent 7+ years building distributed systems, full-stack applications, and developer tools.
      My stack spans TypeScript, Go, Java, and Python — though these days I mostly think in TypeScript and Go.
      I care about architecture, developer experience, and building things that don't fall apart at scale.
    </p>

    <p>
      Right now I'm deep in the world of <strong>AI agents</strong> — not the hype version, but the real engineering
      problems: how do you give agents persistent data? How do they manage permissions? What happens when
      three agents write to the same resource? The boring problems that make the magic possible.
    </p>

    <h2>What I write about</h2>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>AI agents</strong> — the infrastructure layer, not the prompting tricks</li>
      <li><strong>TypeScript & Go</strong> — patterns, opinions, the stuff I learn building real systems</li>
      <li><strong>Platform engineering</strong> — APIs, protocols, developer tools</li>
      <li><strong>Things nobody else is talking about</strong> — the non-obvious observations from building at the edge</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Find me</h2>

